  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ASSISTANT PROJECT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in planning, executing, and monitoring projects to ensure timely delivery within scope, budget, and quality standards. </li><li>Collaborate with stakeholders to drive project success and continuous improvement.</li><li>Develop detailed workstream plans by gathering requirements, allocating resources, and consulting stakeholders to define clear deliverables.</li><li>Monitor project performance against scope, KPIs, budget, schedule, and risks, and obtain approvals for any deviations to maintain project alignment.</li><li>Facilitate effective communication and collaboration among project teams and internal and external stakeholders to ensure seamless project execution.</li><li>Support project close-out activities by conducting post-implementation reviews, documenting lessons learnt, and preparing comprehensive handover materials.</li><li>Demonstrate adaptability by performing additional duties as assigned to support project and organisational goals.</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in Chemical or any Engineering discipline or equivalent</li><li>At least 4 years of experience in a similar project coordination or engineering role</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Valid Class 3 driving licence (advantageous for site visits and project logistics)</li><li>Proficient in MS Office applications to support project documentation and reporting</li><li>Ability to work independently with resourcefulness and strong problem-solving skills</li><li>Effective interpersonal and communication skills to engage diverse teams and stakeholders</li><li>Collaborative team player committed to delivering results with assertiveness and accountability</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Work schedule: 5.5-day work week, Monday to Friday, 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.; Saturday, 8:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m.</li><li>Must be willing to work in the West region of Singapore.<br /></li></ul>",
